version: 1
display_name: VCFH-9X-000061 - The VMware Cloud Foundation Operations Apache HTTP service must restrict the ability of users to launch Denial of Service (DoS) attacks against other information systems or networks.
global_description: |-
  A web server can limit the ability of the web server being used in a DoS attack through several methods. The methods employed will depend upon the hosted applications and their resource needs for proper operation.

  An example setting that could be used to limit the ability of the web server being used in a DoS attack is bandwidth throttling.
osfinger:
  - VMware Photon OS-5
refs:
  disa_stig:
    - VCFH-9X-000061
  srg:
    - SRG-APP-000246-WSR-000149
  cci:
    - CCI-001094
    - CCI-002385
  nist:
    - SC-5 (1)
    - SC-5 a
benchmark_id:
  vcf9_operations_httpd:
    type: custom
    desc: The VMware Cloud Foundation Operations Apache HTTP service must restrict the ability of users to launch Denial of Service (DoS) attacks against other information systems or networks.
    control_id: VCFH-9X-000061
    scored: true
    profile:
      - default
    information: |-
      Verify a timeout is in place.

      At the command prompt, run the following:

      # grep -i "Timeout"  /etc/httpd/conf/httpd.conf /etc/httpd/conf/extra/httpd-ssl.conf /usr/lib/vmware-vcopssuite/utilities/conf/vcops-apache.conf

      Example output:

      TimeOut 60

      If the value of "TimeOut" is set to 0, this is a finding.

      If "TimeOut" does not exist or is commented out, this is not a finding.
    rationale: |-
      A web server can limit the ability of the web server being used in a DoS attack through several methods. The methods employed will depend upon the hosted applications and their resource needs for proper operation.

      An example setting that could be used to limit the ability of the web server being used in a DoS attack is bandwidth throttling.
    remediation: |-
      Navigate to and open:

      /etc/httpd/conf/httpd.conf

      Note: If the offending configuration was found in a different file edit that file instead.

      Remove or update the following lines:

      TimeOut 60

      Reload the configuration by running the following command:

      # systemctl reload httpd
